17/04/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Wednesday (16 April), the Office of the High Representative (OHR) welcomed progress achieved by BiH authorities in implementing the Bulldozer process, which is designed to improve the economy by targeted reforms. Noting the 15-day deadline set by the OHR Bulldozer Committee for enactment of 50 legal amendments expires Monday, the OHR emphasised that the governments and parliaments at all levels have responded constructively to the process.
In other news, Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic wrapped up an official visit to Washington on Wednesday, saying that the United States supports efforts to implement reforms and fight crime. He held a series of meetings with senior US officials and representatives of international financial institutions. (RS government web site - 17/04/03; OHR Sources, Onasa, NTV Hayat, SRNA, BBC - 16/04/03)
